xpack.maps.tutorials.ems.downloadStepTex:
1. Navigate to Elastic Maps Service [landing page]({emsLandingPageUrl}/).
2. In the left sidebar, select an administrative boundary.
3. Click `Download GeoJSON` button.
xpack.maps.tutorials.ems.longDescription: [Elastic Maps Service (EMS)](https://www.elastic.co/elastic-maps-service) hosts tile layers and vector shapes of administrative boundaries. Indexing EMS administrative boundaries in Elasticsearch allows for search on boundary property fields.
xpack.maps.tutorials.ems.shortDescriptio: Administrative boundaries from Elastic Maps Service.
xpack.maps.tutorials.ems.uploadStepText:
1. Open [Maps]({newMapUrl}).
2. Click `Add layer`, then select `Upload GeoJSON`.
3. Upload the GeoJSON file and click `Import file`.
